Pleural effusions can be classified as transudates or exudates based on Lights criteria, which classify an effusion as exudate if one or more of the following are present: 1 the ratio of pleural fluid protein to serum protein is greater than 0.5, 2 the ratio of pleural fluid lactate dehydrogenase LDH to serum LDH is greater than 0.6, or 3 the pleural fluid LDH level is greater than two thirds of the upper limit of normal for serum LDH.
